m of   Donnchadh ."]},{"name":"Donough","meanings":["Anglicized form of   Donnchadh ."]},{"name":"Duncan","meanings":["Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Donnchadh , also used among people without Scottish connections. This was the name of a 7th-century Scottish saint (abbot of Iona) and two medieval kings of Scotland. The final ‐<i>n</i> in the Anglicized form seems to be the result of confusion with the Gaelic word <i>ceann</i> ‘head’ in the Latinized form <i>Duncanus</i>.  Compare Irish  Donagh ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Mael Muir Mac Donnchad Mormaer married Mael Muire Mac Donnchad Mormaer of Atholl before 1068. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1037–1128":"1037–1128","1085–1152":"1085–1152","1087–Male":"1087–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1128":"1128","before 1068":"enne 1068","1037":"1037","1087":"1087","1152":"1152","1085":"1085","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Atholl, Perthshire, Scotland":"Atholl, Perthshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1037–1128":"1037–1128","1085–1152":"1085–1152","1087–Male":"1087–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1128":"1128","before 1068":"ennen vuotta 1068","1037":"1037","1087":"1087","1152":"1152","1085":"1085","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Atholl, Perthshire, Scotland":"Atholl, Perthshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1037–1128":"1037–1128","1085–1152":"1085–1152","1087–Male":"1087–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1128":"1128","before 1068":"avant 1068","1037":"1037","1087":"1087","1152":"1152","1085":"1085","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Atholl, Perthshire, Scotland":"Atholl, Perthshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Mrs Mael Muir Mac Donnchad Mormaer a épousé Mael Muire Mac Donnchad Mormaer of Atholl avant 1068. Ils ont eu au moins 2 fils."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1037–1128":"1037–1128","1085–1152":"1085–1152","1087–Male":"1087–Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1128":"1128","before 1068":"vor 1068","1037":"1037","1087":"1087","1152":